WEBVTT

00:04.440 --> 00:06.738
Hey, hey, hey! Judge!

00:06.909 --> 00:08.536
Any disembowelments tonight?

00:08.711 --> 00:10.269
Not that I know of, no.

00:10.446 --> 00:12.640
Mutilation murders? Bizarre suicides?

00:12.814 --> 00:15.374
Nothing good on TV tonight,
huh, Mr?

00:15.550 --> 00:17.609
- Craven. Al Craven.
- Yeah.

00:17.786 --> 00:21.017
<i>With the Gazette. I did that big
front-page story last week...</i>

00:21.189 --> 00:23.817
...on the lady who fricasseed the poodle.

00:24.392 --> 00:26.917
- AI Craven, the journalist.
- Yeah.

00:27.095 --> 00:30.962
You know, I really like it here in court.
There's always a never-ending supply...

00:31.131 --> 00:33.691
...of human misery in a place like this.
- Yeah.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.529
Most people don't see the fun side
of pain and suffering.

00:36.704 --> 00:38.604
Right.

00:39.573 --> 00:41.473
See you.

00:44.010 --> 00:45.307
Cute kid, the judge.

00:45.478 --> 00:48.208
Well, we think so,
but he's not exactly a kid.

00:48.381 --> 00:49.712
- Is this seat taken?
- Yes.

00:49.882 --> 00:51.315
Thank you.

00:52.285 --> 00:54.480
He doesn't even look old enough
to use a razor.

00:54.654 --> 00:57.487
Oh, and speaking of razors,
you would be revolted...

00:57.657 --> 01:00.625
...at what I've seen a razor do
to the human body.

01:02.761 --> 01:05.628
Be that as it may, Judge Stone
is older than you think.

01:05.797 --> 01:07.662
Well, how old is he?

01:07.833 --> 01:10.859
Well, he's... I don't know.
How old do you think he is, Dan?

01:11.436 --> 01:14.233
I don't know. It's one of those things
I never think about...

01:14.405 --> 01:16.771
...like "Is Pinky Lee still alive?"

01:17.375 --> 01:19.969
I'm sure you gotta be a minimum age
to be a judge.

01:20.144 --> 01:23.045
No, you have to have been practicing law
for at least 10 years.

01:23.214 --> 01:25.614
- I think he's about...
- Say, here's a novel approach:

01:25.783 --> 01:28.911
- Why don't we ask him. Judge Stone.
- Yo.

01:29.086 --> 01:32.145
We were just talking, and we're
a little curious. What is your age?

01:32.322 --> 01:34.620
Oh, I'm a little over 900 years old.

01:35.792 --> 01:37.953
That's what a spiritualist
once told me, anyway.

01:38.128 --> 01:40.722
Seems I have this very old soul.

01:41.331 --> 01:43.595
The first couple hundred years
are sort of a blur.

01:43.767 --> 01:46.530
- I know how you feel.
- Yeah.

01:46.702 --> 01:48.761
- Bye.
- See you.

01:50.572 --> 01:52.096
- Colorful guy.
- I'm telling you...

01:52.274 --> 01:55.334
...he has a few pages stuck together.

01:55.511 --> 01:56.739
Wanna talk crazy?

01:56.912 --> 01:59.574
You read the piece I did about the guy
who went berserk...

01:59.748 --> 02:01.738
...and turned his loved ones
into lunchmeat?

02:03.818 --> 02:08.084
Well, you'll have to excuse me.
All this lunch talk is making me hungry.

02:09.190 --> 02:11.681
I guess the judge is in his 20s.

02:11.859 --> 02:13.827
I say he's close to 40.

02:13.995 --> 02:16.292
In dog years, maybe.

02:16.596 --> 02:20.430
- I'll bet you 5 he's 28.
- You're on.

02:20.600 --> 02:22.591
- You got a bet.
- You're both acting selfish.

02:22.769 --> 02:25.203
Why don't we get a pool together
so we can all play.

02:25.539 --> 02:27.837
- Hey, now, that sounds good to me.
- Excuse me.

02:28.008 --> 02:30.840
How are you gonna determine the winner
if he won't tell his age.

02:31.010 --> 02:32.637
There's gotta be ways to find out.

02:32.812 --> 02:35.781
We could saw him in half
and count the rings.

02:36.515 --> 02:38.847
No. Hey, it's gotta be a matter
of public record...

02:39.018 --> 02:41.418
...like civil service forms or whatever,
right, Lana?

02:41.587 --> 02:43.020
- Yeah.
- Easily, Lana.

02:43.189 --> 02:46.988
Oh, I suppose I could call downtown
and get a look at his personnel file.

02:47.158 --> 02:50.719
It's settled. I'll make up the sign-up
sheet and we'll pick the ages we want.

02:50.895 --> 02:52.123
- I'm in.
- Good.

02:52.297 --> 02:54.629
- I don't know.
- Oh, it'll be fun.

02:54.799 --> 02:56.699
I feel like we're prying.

02:56.868 --> 02:58.995
That's the fun part.

02:59.904 --> 03:04.340
I really don't understand society's
preoccupation with age in the first place.

03:04.508 --> 03:07.204
I mean, you're only as old as you feel,
right, Selma?

03:07.378 --> 03:08.743
That's vicious.

